HEADWORD: pam
<hw>pam</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Palm</er>
victory; cf. <ets>trump</ets>, fr. <ets>triumph</ets>, and perh. fr. F.
<ets>pamphile</ets> from Pamphile, a man's name.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The knave of clubs.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A card game in which the jack of clubs is
